title: Millburn High School-Cedar Grove High School football game postponed to Oct. 10
text:
Buy this photo staff photo by jim connelly Wes Moshier (20) and the Millburn High School varsity football team will take on Cedar Grove High School Saturday, Oct. 10, at 6 p.m. at Millburn High School's Dr. Keith A. Neigel Field after tonight's Super Essex Conference, Colonial Division opener for both squads was postponed due to inclement weather. 
Tonight's football game between host Millburn High School and Cedar Grove High School has been postponed on account of thunderstorms that rolled through the area early this evening. 
The decision to postpone the game was announced by Ted D'Alessio, Millburn's director of athletics some 20 minutes past the scheduled 7 p.m. kickoff. 
The Super Essex Conference, Colonial Division opener between the 3-0 Millers and 3-1 Panthers has been rescheduled for Saturday, Oct. 10, at 6 p.m. at Millburn High School's Dr. Keith A. Neigel Field.
